    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen using the latest neovim version, I am getting many deprecation warnings for lua functions used by plugins I have installed. There is no way to fix/update the deprecated functions until the plugin maintainer updates their upstream. So, this leaves me having to keep dealing with deprecation warnings popups.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n`nvim` should support a flag `--suppress-deprecation-warnings` to ignore the deprecation warnings",
