            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I believe that's one of the purposes of nightly and devel versions. If you find it's annoying and interferes with your workflow, you should stick to a stable release (0.10) version instead of HEAD/nightly versions. Warnings are actually useful, although it may seem a bit inconvenient for end users, because with the \"hard deprecation\" warnings plugin authors are strongly encouraged to fix the deprecated API as soon as possible while in the development cycle and before the full release.\r\n\r\nAs a last resort, you may want to monkey-patch those deprecated Lua functions (e.g. `vim.tbl_islist = vim.islist`), or even `vim.deprecate` to suppress all warnings, in your config or via command line arguments to `nvim`.",
